
-- In order to get GHCi to work, `stack ghci` should be passed the flag
-- `--ghci-options "-XNoImplicitPrelude"`.  Then, we have to set the
-- `ImplicitPrelude` option when GHCi finally loads.  This is an annoying
-- work-around for GHCi's inability to use alternative Preludes easily.
-- https://ghc.haskell.org/trac/ghc/ticket/10920
:set -XImplicitPrelude
